{
  "stem": "21308.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, this would be [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] late 20s, late 20s, at the very beginning of the 30s, late 20s.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But it was a very great evening service the-- from St.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Martin-in-the-Fields which was in Trafalgar Square.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, after I left school, we knew-- and the papers gave us news-- of the Japanese aggression in China, which was the first thing we saw.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we knew of the discontent in Germany and Europe, which was the results of the second-- of the First World War and the Treaty of Versailles.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the-- we watched with more than passing interest the rise of the struggle in Germany for power.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- but of course, the news we got was heavily filtered.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And above all, we had to earn our living.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I'm afraid we didn't get involved in a lot of politics.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My MP at the time-- and I remember him coming to the village with Dolly, his wife-- was James de Rothschild.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he lived in a place called Waddesdon Manor near Tring some miles to the south in-- I think in Buckinghamshire it is.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But we knew that things were bad, because by 1934, I decided I wanted to be a policeman.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the only way to become a policeman was to join the army and to do a tour of duty in the army.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And if you did that and did well of it, it was almost note and take it into police, providing the police had vacancies.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And there was always police, and like the Metropolitan Police, which was reckoned to be the best police force in the world at that time.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then, as now, they didn't carry arms, except on special mission.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[COUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
